{% extends '../_includes/layout.njk' %}

{% block content %}
    <article>
        <section>
            <h2 class="toc__heading" style="display: none" id="intro">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="intro">Historically at Justworks, we've used a single UI component, <strong>tabs</strong>, to fulfill several different use cases. To help people better recognize these distinct use cases, we should instead use visually-distinct components to represent them.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="toc__heading" id="tabs">Tabs</h2>
            <p>Tabs are used to separate distinct panes of content, and only show one of them at a time.</p>
            <p>The horizontal line under a set of tabs is used to indicate that those tabs control the content below them. This means that:</p>
            <ul class="bulleted-list">
                <li>tabs should not control the content above, to the left, or to the right of them</li>
                <li>there should not be content below the tabs, in the same container, that the tabs do not control</li>
            </ul>

            {% call figure() %}
                <picture>
                    <source
                        srcset="/assets/img/patterns/tabs-and-friends/tabs-dark.png"
                        media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
                    />
                    <img
                        style="width: 30rem; margin: 0 auto"
                        src="/assets/img/patterns/tabs-and-friends/tabs.png"
                        alt="A diagram visualizing that tabs control what's below them, but not above, to the left, or to the right"
                    />
                </picture>
            {% endcall %}
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2 class="toc__heading" id="segmented-controls">Segmented controls</h2>
            <p>Segmented controls are used to show a specific subset of a larger collection of items, that are all displayed in the same way.</p>
            <p>In other words, they function as a filter on a list of items. So it's usually a good idea to have one of the controls show the entire list.</p>

            {% call figure() %}
                <picture>
                    <source
                        srcset="/assets/img/patterns/tabs-and-friends/segmented-controls-1-dark.png"
                        media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
                    />
                    <img
                        style="width: 30rem; margin: 0 auto"
